title: For Sale:  Smith and Wesson Model 1911PD Gunsite edition 45 acp
postcontent:
This is the increasingly difficult to find Smith & Wesson 1911PD Gunsite Edition pistol. 

The lusterous blueing on the slide, barrel and other hard parts is nicely contrasted by the lovely walnut stocks with the carved S&W and Gunsite Raven logo's which is echoed in the Raven engraving on the receiver. The frame is made from Scandium. The sights are Novak low rise and make for a smooth, no snag draw from a holster (no front gold bead). The barrel is 4 1/4" with a match grade barrel bushing. The trigger is adjustable. The gun comes in the factory lockable protective case with the original manual, barrel wrench, 2 S&W OEM ACT made, 8 round magazines and sealed packet containing the sample factory fired casing. 

I am the original owner and have fired this very accurate pistol less than 100 rounds of Federal and RP 45 ACP hardball. The earlier manufactured pistols like this one (SN FSP 0798) were completely hand fitted for maximum accuracy and reliability. The gun is in completely stock, unmodified condition since new. I will offer approximately 2 and 1/2 boxes of new RP (2 boxes of 50 rounds 230gr RN, approximately 1/2 box of Federal 230gr RN) to the buyer at my cost from about a year ago.

I play by the rules. For sale face to face only to bonafide Arkansas resident with proof of Ar residency, otherwise it has to go through (or sale to) an FFL. 

I also believe in describing an item accurately. Feel free to check my feedback on ebay (handle- achildofthesky )I am an individual and not a dealer or business and because of this, the gun is sold with out warranties of any type on my part and all sales are final. That said, if you have been looking for a truely nice example of these accurate and finely assembled and increasingly hard to find pistols, you will not be dissapointed with this one.  I have a couple of other high quality collectable guns I will be selling to help generate funds for a home purchase.

2004 Marlin 336Y Spikehorn carbine in 30-30 Winchester, very, very nice rifle! 
This gun has been fired less than 3 boxes of ammo since new and still has that "new gun" feel to it with the action a nice snug feel to it. I do not have the original box for it. This is the increasingly difficult to find original, made only from 2002-2004 (made in limited numbers) Connecticut made JM 336Y Spikehorn with 16 1/4" trapper length barrel and a 1 inch shorter length of pull stock that is perfect for smaller stature shooters but also makes it a fine choice for all that appreciate a handy handling, all around rifle. 

The lusterous blueing on the receiver, barrel and other hard parts is nicely contrasted by the lovely walnut stocks. The exceptionally nice smooth, pistol grip buttstock and fore end are made from genuine deep and rich walnut (not some mystery wood or laminate like the horrid REMLIN rifles currently on sale) in excellent condition and the rifle wears the OEM factory recoil pad. The receiver is factory drilled and tapped for scope mounts. I will offer a buyer the option of a quality scope mount installed in place of the WGRS peep sight should they so desire. 

The sights are a Williams WGRS in the rear (windage and elevation adjustable peep sight with screw in aperture) and the appropriate height Williams Fire Sight front sight and also the factory rear sight is in place which is adjustable for windage and elevation of course. This would make a truely great fast handling deer & bear rifle for the woods hunter and also a fine first rifle for young hunters.

title: For Sale:  BUFFALO-BARNES .45 ACP +P LEAD FREE - 185 gr. TAC-XP LOW FLASH (1,150 fps) - 20 Round Box
postcontent:
http://extreme-impact-ammo.com/index.php?l=product_detail&p=299

This load is a very high performance +P 45 acp load. The 185gr. hollow cavity Barnes all copper bullet mushrooms readily and still penetrates deeply for such a light bullet, while giving the low recoil and high velocity of a light bullet. This helps fast sight acquisition for quick/accurate follow-up shots. Expect roughly 13 to 14 inches of penetration in flesh and bone.

This load utilizes a low flash powder which gives an important tactical advantage to the shooter as most shootings in the US occur in low light when the criminal element is most active. Being blinded by your own gunfire after the first shot, leaves you very vulnerable.

As usual, Buffalo Bore tests and obtains our advertised velocities from real world over-the-counter firearms. We believe that the industry wide established practice of utilizing extra long test barrels to generate advertised velocities is dishonest and creates expectations that cannot be realized in real guns, in the real world, where it matters. With Buffalo Bore ammo, you’ll actually obtain the velocities we advertise.

    1193 fps -- Colt Series 90 Gold Cup, 5 inch
    1183 fps -- H&K, USP Tactical, 5 inch
    1158 fps -- Glock Model 21, 4.6 inch
    1159 fps -- Colt series 80 Commander, 4.25 inch
    1110 fps -- Glock model 30, 3.5 inch


In one of the above instances, you’ll note that a longer barrel gave velocities lower than one of the shorter barrels, showing that there is more to internal ballistics, than just barrel length.

This load reliably fed and exhibited very good accuracy in all test pistols.
